219
00:16:52,133 --> 00:16:55,136
Hang on a second, Dave.
Hi, I’m Michael Drucker.
You must be Adam Gibson.

220
00:16:55,171 --> 00:16:57,604
That's right.
Adam's the name
and flying's the game.

221
00:16:57,639 --> 00:17:00,892
Pete Hume speaks highly of you.
He says you know
the mountains like nobody else.

222
00:17:00,927 --> 00:17:04,145
Thank you. That's probably
true for everyone except
my partner, but thank you.

223
00:17:04,180 --> 00:17:06,147
I'm looking forward to it.
So, we all set?
Yes, sir.

224
00:17:06,648 --> 00:17:10,151
We've stationed our people
monitoring the rescue beacons...
don't need the details.

225
00:17:10,186 --> 00:17:13,154
All right!
Your favorite snowboard's
behind your seat, sir.

226
00:17:13,189 --> 00:17:17,123
Dave, look, we gave a lot
of money to his campaign,

227
00:17:17,158 --> 00:17:20,662
not to mention what
I pay your law firm,
so I’m counting on you.

228
00:17:20,697 --> 00:17:23,682
Are you gonna get me
the speaker? Good.

229
00:17:23,717 --> 00:17:26,668
So, sally, who's next?
Okay, put him on.

230
00:17:56,197 --> 00:17:59,200
You own the roadrunners,
right?

231
00:18:01,703 --> 00:18:03,204
[Gunshot]

232
00:18:15,216 --> 00:18:20,221
Hey, buddy, wake up.
Wake up! We're here.
Woodland mall.

233
00:18:27,228 --> 00:18:30,196
Oh.

234
00:18:30,231 --> 00:18:32,233
I was asleep.

235
00:18:35,737 --> 00:18:38,239
[Female over p.a. System]
Welcome to woodland mall.

236
00:18:38,274 --> 00:18:41,242
Over 1200 retail outlets
to serve you.

237
00:18:41,277 --> 00:18:43,745
Food court, ground level.

238
00:18:46,247 --> 00:18:48,715
[Man]
Stop the cloning.
Say no to RePet.

239
00:18:48,750 --> 00:18:52,218
Stop the cloning.
Say no to RePet.
Stop the cloning.

240
00:18:52,253 --> 00:18:54,756
Save your soul, man.
God doesn't want you
to go in there.

241
00:18:54,791 --> 00:18:57,759
Then god shouldn't have killed
my dog.
Atheist.

242
00:18:57,794 --> 00:19:00,727
Stop the cloning.
Say no to RePet.

243
00:19:00,762 --> 00:19:04,265
We can clone your
four-legged loved one
in just a few short hours.

244
00:19:04,300 --> 00:19:08,269
How can we do it?
It all begins with
the growing of blanks,

245
00:19:08,304 --> 00:19:10,772
animal drones
stripped of all
characteristic D.N.A.,

246
00:19:10,807 --> 00:19:13,740
in embryonic tanks
at the RePet factory.

247
00:19:13,775 --> 00:19:18,279
In stage two, your pet's D.N.A.
is extracted from a lock of fur
or drop of blood...

248
00:19:18,314 --> 00:19:22,248
and then infused
on a cellular level
into the blank.

249
00:19:22,283 --> 00:19:25,787
In the final stage,
using RePet's patented
cerebral syncording process,

250
00:19:25,822 --> 00:19:28,790
all of your pet's thoughts,
memories and instincts...

251
00:19:28,825 --> 00:19:31,292
are painlessly transplanted
via the optic nerve.

252
00:19:31,327 --> 00:19:36,297
Still can't make up
your mind, huh?

253
00:19:36,332 --> 00:19:38,765
You lost a dog, right?

254
00:19:38,800 --> 00:19:42,053
Yes. My daughter's.
Oh, what a heartbreak.

255
00:19:42,088 --> 00:19:45,306
What'd you say
his name was again?
Oliver.

256
00:19:45,807 --> 00:19:51,312
Well, Oliver’s in luck.
We're having a special
this week, 20% off.

257
00:19:51,347 --> 00:19:53,815
When did Oliver die?
Sometime this morning.

258
00:19:54,315 --> 00:19:56,282
That's perfect.
We can still do
a postmortem syncording.

259
00:19:56,317 --> 00:19:59,821
But you've got to act fast.
'Cause there's only a 12-hour
window on deceased brains.

260
00:19:59,856 --> 00:20:02,323
I have a problem
with that whole idea.

261
00:20:02,824 --> 00:20:05,291
I mean, suppose
that clones have no soul,
or they're dangerous.

262
00:20:05,326 --> 00:20:10,832
Clone pets are every bit
as safe as real pets.
Plus... they're insured.

263
00:20:11,332 --> 00:20:15,837
If it is so safe,
then why is it against the law
to clone human beings?

264
00:20:15,872 --> 00:20:18,840
Because the human brain
is much too complicated
to syncord.

265
00:20:18,875 --> 00:20:20,807
Now, you remember that
experiment they did, right?

266
00:20:20,842 --> 00:20:24,846
Yes.
That's why that didn't work.
Now it's illegal to even try.

267
00:20:24,881 --> 00:20:27,849
But with pets,
it's a totally proven
technology.

268
00:20:28,349 --> 00:20:31,818
Your RePet, Oliver, will be
exactly the same dog.

269
00:20:31,853 --> 00:20:36,357
He'll know all the
same tricks you taught him,
where the bones are buried.

270
00:20:36,392 --> 00:20:41,362
He won't even know he's a clone.
And, did I mention?
They're insured.

271
00:20:41,397 --> 00:20:43,329
I don't care about
the insurance.

272
00:20:43,364 --> 00:20:46,868
I care about if I can trust
my daughter with a large animal
with sharp teeth.

273
00:20:46,903 --> 00:20:51,372
We can make him smaller
if you want, with softer teeth.
You can?

274
00:20:51,873 --> 00:20:55,842
We can even color coordinate him
to match your decorating scheme.

275
00:20:55,877 --> 00:20:59,380
- [P.a. System] sim-pal,
the best friend money can buy.
- Let me think about that.

276
00:20:59,881 --> 00:21:04,385
- Treat your kids
to a sim-pal today.
- I might be back.

277
00:21:04,420 --> 00:21:06,352
You'll be back.

278
00:21:06,387 --> 00:21:08,855
Your daughter will think
you're the best dad.

279
00:21:08,890 --> 00:21:12,393
My kid sister has two of
these, and she loves them.
Oh, good.

280
00:21:12,428 --> 00:21:15,413
Let's fix the collar.
There you are.

281
00:21:15,448 --> 00:21:18,364
It's amazing
how real this is.
I know.

282
00:21:18,399 --> 00:21:22,403
My daughter will be so excited.
Come, let's go home.

283
00:21:28,526 --> 00:21:33,531
- [Female phone operator]
You have called Hank Morgan.
- I'm not here. Leave a message.

284
00:21:33,566 --> 00:21:35,498
Hank, it's me again.
What the hell happened
to you?

285
00:21:35,533 --> 00:21:39,037
I waited at Kelly’s
for over half an hour.
It's now five past seven.

286
00:21:39,537 --> 00:21:43,506
I'm Sim-Pal Cindy.
What's your name?

287
00:21:43,541 --> 00:21:48,046
Look, I’m heading home.
If you get this message...
let's be friends.

288
00:21:48,081 --> 00:21:52,515
What's your name?
Just... can't you see
I’m talking? Quiet.

289
00:21:52,550 --> 00:21:55,553
Head over to my house
with a bunch of flowers
and a good excuse.

290
00:21:55,588 --> 00:21:57,520
Otherwise Natalie's
gonna kill you.

291
00:21:57,555 --> 00:22:00,808
I can sing songs.
Would you like to sing with me?

292
00:22:00,843 --> 00:22:04,027
Excuse me.
Do you know how
to turn this thing off?

293
00:22:04,062 --> 00:22:07,565
- I can play games.
- My niece has one.
Say, "go to sleep, Cindy."

294
00:22:08,066 --> 00:22:11,069
Go to sleep, Cindy.
I can sing songs.
Would you like to sing with me?

295
00:22:11,104 --> 00:22:13,071
Go to sleep.

296
00:22:21,579 --> 00:22:25,083
Thank you.
Thanks for the ride.
Good night.

297
00:22:35,093 --> 00:22:37,560
Clara, sweetie, honey.

298
00:22:37,595 --> 00:22:41,599
Oliver was very sick,
and he had to be put down.

299
00:22:44,602 --> 00:22:48,606
Clara, sweetie, honey.
Oliver had to go to heaven.

300
00:22:49,107 --> 00:22:50,608
"Why, daddy?"

301
00:22:51,109 --> 00:22:53,611
You see, it's because...

302
00:22:54,112 --> 00:22:57,580
it's because...

303
00:22:57,615 --> 00:22:59,617
oh, shit, Oliver!
Why did you have to die?

304
00:22:59,652 --> 00:23:02,137
[Barking]

305
00:23:02,172 --> 00:23:05,149
Oliver?

306
00:23:05,184 --> 00:23:08,126
[Barking]

307
00:23:11,129 --> 00:23:13,131
Natalie.

308
00:23:17,135 --> 00:23:21,889
# Happy birthday to you #

309
00:23:21,924 --> 00:23:27,037
# Happy birthday dear Adam #

310
00:23:27,072 --> 00:23:32,150
# Happy birthday to you ##

311
00:23:32,185 --> 00:23:34,920
[Laughing, cheering]

312
00:23:34,955 --> 00:23:37,655
I know. Can you help me?

313
00:23:37,690 --> 00:23:41,159
One, two, three!

314
00:23:41,194 --> 00:23:45,128
[Cheering]

315
00:23:45,163 --> 00:23:48,666
Look at this cake here!
I know!

316
00:23:50,168 --> 00:23:51,669
Oh, my god!

317
00:24:14,692 --> 00:24:17,660
- Adam Gibson?
- Who are you?

318
00:24:17,695 --> 00:24:20,698
We have a little situation.
Will you come with us?

319
00:24:20,733 --> 00:24:23,166
What the hell
is going on here?

320
00:24:23,201 --> 00:24:25,668
Just cooperate
and everything will be fine.

321
00:24:25,703 --> 00:24:28,706
Fine? There's someone
in my house,
eating my birthday cake...

322
00:24:28,741 --> 00:24:31,674
with my family,
and it's not me!
We know.

323
00:24:31,709 --> 00:24:35,213
There's been
a sixth day violation.
A human was cloned.

324
00:24:35,248 --> 00:24:38,181
That human was you.
We can help you.

325
00:24:38,216 --> 00:24:41,219
- Then get him out of there!
- But you'll have to come
with us.

326
00:24:41,719 --> 00:24:45,723
Look, I don't know
who the hell you people are.

327
00:24:46,224 --> 00:24:48,226
But I’m going inside
my house.

328
00:24:48,261 --> 00:24:50,228
Yeah, right.

329
00:24:59,737 --> 00:25:03,741
- Oops. Cindy fell down.
- Get the doll.

330
00:25:08,246 --> 00:25:12,250
Not here!

331
00:25:22,260 --> 00:25:25,763
I'm Sim-Pal Cindy.
What's your name?

332
00:25:29,767 --> 00:25:32,770
[Cindy]
I can play games.

333
00:25:33,771 --> 00:25:36,774
- [Grunts]
- [Zapper zapping]

334
00:25:44,282 --> 00:25:46,284
- Shit!
- [Gunshot]

335
00:25:49,787 --> 00:25:54,792
Wiley, no, hold your fire!
That way! Go!
Vincent, go!

336
00:25:54,827 --> 00:25:57,295
I have a boo-boo.

337
00:26:14,812 --> 00:26:17,815
Stop the car!
Stop the car!

338
00:26:20,818 --> 00:26:25,323
Thanks for the suggestion!
Don't even blink.

339
00:26:25,823 --> 00:26:28,326
Oh, my god.
Someone stole the minivan.

340
00:26:28,361 --> 00:26:30,828
They stole my Cadillac!

341
00:26:32,330 --> 00:26:33,831
Oh, no!

342
00:26:40,338 --> 00:26:42,340
Car chase. Cool!

343
00:26:45,343 --> 00:26:47,310
[Yelling]

344
00:26:47,345 --> 00:26:51,849
- Who are you?
- I was hired to kill you.
That's all I know!

345
00:26:53,351 --> 00:26:56,319
I'm Sim-Pal Cindy.
What's your name?

346
00:26:56,354 --> 00:26:58,856
[Electronic voice]
Please secure
child seat restraint.

347
00:26:58,891 --> 00:27:01,859
Let's be friends.

348
00:27:16,874 --> 00:27:19,377
- Where is this guy?
- I'm Sim-Pal Cindy.

349
00:27:19,877 --> 00:27:21,879
- Shh.
- Let's be friends.
- Shh.

350
00:27:21,914 --> 00:27:24,847
What's your name?

351
00:27:24,882 --> 00:27:27,885
- Will you be my mommy?
- I don't wanna be your mommy!

352
00:27:27,920 --> 00:27:29,387
- Shut up!
- What?

353
00:27:29,887 --> 00:27:31,854
[Crying]

354
00:27:31,889 --> 00:27:33,856
[Brakes squeal]

355
00:27:33,891 --> 00:27:35,893
Somebody do something
about that damn doll!

356
00:27:40,898 --> 00:27:43,901
I have a boo-boo.

357
00:27:47,405 --> 00:27:49,372
[Screaming]

358
00:27:49,407 --> 00:27:54,377
This is crazy.
Why does anyone want
to kill me?

359
00:27:54,412 --> 00:27:58,881
He got home first.
You saw him. He didn't see you.
You're screwed.

360
00:27:58,916 --> 00:28:03,421
He's gonna live out the rest
of your boring little life
and never be the wiser.

361
00:28:03,456 --> 00:28:07,425
Your wife and kid see you
and him together,
they'll be killed.

362
00:28:09,427 --> 00:28:11,429
[Screams]

363
00:28:22,940 --> 00:28:25,443
- Whoa!
- [Horn honking]

364
00:28:27,445 --> 00:28:29,447
- Oh, shit!
- [Horn honking]

365
00:28:46,464 --> 00:28:48,466
No!
[Groans]

366
00:28:52,470 --> 00:28:55,473
Goddamn it, Wiley!

367
00:28:55,973 --> 00:28:58,476
Son of a bitch!

368
00:29:15,993 --> 00:29:18,996
Stupid!
Blow out his tires this time!

369
00:29:26,504 --> 00:29:30,007
Oh... shit!

370
00:29:37,014 --> 00:29:39,517
Yes!

371
00:30:06,544 --> 00:30:08,546
[Laughing]

372
00:30:11,048 --> 00:30:13,551
[Vincent]
That was spectacular.

373
00:30:31,068 --> 00:30:34,572
Oh, son of a bitch.
Hold my belt.

374
00:30:36,073 --> 00:30:39,076
- Okay.
- [Grunting]

375
00:30:41,579 --> 00:30:43,581
You got me?
Yeah.

376
00:30:45,583 --> 00:30:48,085
Little more.

377
00:30:56,093 --> 00:30:58,095
Oh!

378
00:31:08,606 --> 00:31:10,573
[Chuckles]

379
00:31:10,608 --> 00:31:15,077
Let's get some people downriver
and look for this guy.

380
00:31:15,112 --> 00:31:19,116
Go pick up Wiley
and Talia's bodies,
get 'em back to the lab.

381
00:31:33,631 --> 00:31:36,634
[Protestors]
Weir clinic, stay away!

382
00:31:36,669 --> 00:31:38,636
Hello, I’m dr. Griffin Weir.

383
00:31:39,136 --> 00:31:42,104
Welcome to the new home
of the Weir organ
transplant facility...

384
00:31:42,139 --> 00:31:46,644
thanks for visiting
replacement technologies.
We're in the business of life.

385
00:31:46,679 --> 00:31:49,647
[Female reporter]
Dr. Weir, protestors claim
cloning human organs...

386
00:31:49,682 --> 00:31:51,614
will inevitably lead
to cloning whole humans.

387
00:31:51,649 --> 00:31:56,153
That's not only illegal,
but we're years away from
the technical ability to do it.

388
00:31:56,188 --> 00:31:58,656
But a human was cloned
over ten years ago, doctor.

389
00:31:59,156 --> 00:32:01,123
And we all know the outcome
of that bizarre experiment.

390
00:32:01,158 --> 00:32:05,663
If you recall, the supreme court
ordered that the clone
be destroyed, and I think...

391
00:32:06,163 --> 00:32:08,666
that under the conditions,
it was the humane thing to do.

392
00:32:08,701 --> 00:32:10,633
It led to the laws
against human cloning...

393
00:32:10,668 --> 00:32:14,171
and set back the course
of legitimate research
by many years.

394
00:32:14,672 --> 00:32:17,174
Mr. Drucker? Mr. Drucker?
You gave $100 million...

395
00:32:17,209 --> 00:32:19,141
this is dr. Weir's night.

396
00:32:19,176 --> 00:32:22,179
Dr. Weir, is it true
that you're trying to get
the sixth day laws repealed?

397
00:32:22,214 --> 00:32:25,147
Dr. Weir is interested
in medicine, not politics.

398
00:32:25,182 --> 00:32:29,186
Mr. Drucker,
the protesters outside claim
that you run RePet at a loss...

399
00:32:29,687 --> 00:32:32,189
in order to soften people up
to the idea of human cloning.

400
00:32:32,224 --> 00:32:35,157
You know, we shouldn't forget
that not so long ago...

401
00:32:35,192 --> 00:32:38,661
there were literally
almost no more fish
left in the ocean.

402
00:32:38,696 --> 00:32:42,199
And half the world's population
faced a very real threat
of hunger.

403
00:32:42,234 --> 00:32:44,201
Our cloning technology
helped turn that around.

404
00:32:44,702 --> 00:32:46,669
The extremists
don't like to admit...

405
00:32:46,704 --> 00:32:49,206
that they'd rather
the world went hungry
than eat cloned fish.

406
00:32:49,241 --> 00:32:51,173
So instead they keep yelling
about human cloning.

407
00:32:51,208 --> 00:32:53,676
Do you think
the human cloning laws
should be changed?

408
00:32:53,711 --> 00:32:59,216
Suppose a ten-year-old boy lies
in a hospital bed
dying of liver cancer.

409
00:32:59,251 --> 00:33:03,686
Thanks to dr. Weir's work,
we can save that boy.

410
00:33:03,721 --> 00:33:06,223
Now, in the next bed lies
another ten-year-old boy...

411
00:33:06,258 --> 00:33:08,691
whose parents
love him just as much.

412
00:33:08,726 --> 00:33:11,228
Only this child has
an inoperable brain tumor.

413
00:33:11,729 --> 00:33:14,196
Now, you cannot clone
a brain.

414
00:33:14,231 --> 00:33:17,700
The only way to save him
would be to clone
the whole person.

415
00:33:17,735 --> 00:33:21,739
How do you tell
that boy's parents
that we can save the first boy,

416
00:33:22,239 --> 00:33:24,206
but the research
that would have saved their son,

417
00:33:24,241 --> 00:33:28,746
it wasn't done because of a law
that was passed by frightened
politicians a decade ago?

418
00:33:28,781 --> 00:33:31,248
So what does that mean?

419
00:33:31,283 --> 00:33:32,750
Enjoy the party.

420
00:33:40,758 --> 00:33:44,261
Looked like you needed rescuing.
Yes, Michael, I did.
Thank you.

421
00:33:44,296 --> 00:33:49,534
[Chanting]
Weir clinic, stay away!
No research on D.N. A!

422
00:33:49,569 --> 00:33:54,772
[Chanting]
Weir clinic, stay away!
No research on D.N. A!

423
00:33:55,773 --> 00:33:59,276
- [Johnny Phoenix]
Hey, boss!
- Johnny!

424
00:33:59,311 --> 00:34:01,243
How's my star quarterback?

425
00:34:01,278 --> 00:34:06,283
I'd say I was feeling like
a million bucks, except
I’d hate to take a cut in pay.

426
00:34:06,318 --> 00:34:08,751
Don't remind me,
all right?

427
00:34:08,786 --> 00:34:11,253
That was one nasty hit
you took last week.

428
00:34:11,288 --> 00:34:14,792
Be careful, son.
We don't want you
getting killed out there.

429
00:34:14,827 --> 00:34:17,760
Katherine?
You all right?

430
00:34:17,795 --> 00:34:20,297
I'm just feeling...
like I don't quite belong.

431
00:34:20,332 --> 00:34:23,300
No, no.
But I’m fine.
Really I am.

432
00:34:23,335 --> 00:34:25,267
No, you're not.

433
00:34:25,302 --> 00:34:29,807
Should I call dr. Stevens?
No, no, no. No, no.
I just overdid it, that's all.

434
00:34:29,842 --> 00:34:33,811
I'll get a car
to take you home, okay?
Thank you.

435
00:34:37,314 --> 00:34:41,784
[Drucker]
Mr. Speaker, thank you so much
for coming. Champagne?

436
00:34:41,819 --> 00:34:45,823
That was quite a speech.
You heard that? I didn't mean
to get carried away.

437
00:34:45,858 --> 00:34:48,290
Your words meant
a great deal to me.

438
00:34:48,325 --> 00:34:52,329
You see, as it happens,
I have a son with an
inoperable tumor of the brain.

439
00:34:52,364 --> 00:34:55,833
Oh, my god!
I'm so sorry, sir.

440
00:34:56,333 --> 00:34:59,336
Must've been in my subconscious,
knowing you were here, but I
never meant for you to overhear.

441
00:34:59,371 --> 00:35:01,606
No, no,
it's quite all right.

442
00:35:01,641 --> 00:35:03,806
